  "nursesNote": "In group therapy several members meet with a leader to work on shared concerns. Benefits (therapeutic factors) include universality (realizing one is not alone), instillation of hope (seeing others improve), altruism (helping fellow members), sharing information, catharsis, and cohesion (belonging). The leader sets clear norms early (respect, one person speaks at a time, confidentiality that stays within the group), keeps the group on task, encourages participation, and ensures safety. The nurse gently redirects a member who monopolizes so others can share, and invites a silent member to contribute without forcing them. Confidentiality and a supportive, nonjudgmental atmosphere build the trust that makes the group work.",
